'''Brian Kibambe Cipenga''' (born 11 March 1998) is a Congolese [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Midfielder#Winger|left winger]] for Spanish club [[CD Castellón]] and the [[DR Congo national football team|DR Congo national team]].

==Career==
Born in [[Kinshasa]], Cipenga moved to Portugal at early age, and was a [[Boavista F.C.|Boavista FC]] youth graduate. After making his senior debut with the reserves in the 2017–18 season, he moved to fellow [[Porto Football Association|Porto FA]] Elite Division side [[S.C. Freamunde|SC Freamunde]] in 2018.

In 2019, Cipenga joined [[F.C. Famalicão|FC Famalicão]], but only featured for their under-23 team in the {{ill|Liga Revelação|pt}}. On 16 July 2020, he signed for [[Campeonato de Portugal (league)|Campeonato de Portugal]] side [[S.C. Ideal|SC Ideal]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/scideal/photos/a.247268492036497/3135571016539549/?type=3&eid=ARDy3eJFM3eDLzMmj1U-89t6hLyJC9pbnSBnIjOVQnMM6DWQdb-MQpMMLj8aeO-thV1EYgGmi5OAtU2q&ifg=1&locale=he_IL&paipv=0&eav=Afa9tZ68uYZ1pDr-9VUK8aLvA5iFt2DrvKKWtpwiGRmtfQ24S1m1yBeitK-QgBSDHV0&_rdr|title=CONTRATAÇÃO PARA A ÉPOCA 2020–2021|trans-title=SIGNING FOR THE 2020–2021 SEASON|publisher=[[Facebook]]|work=SC Ideal|language=pt|date=16 July 2020|accessdate=8 July 2024}}</ref>

In July 2021, Cipenga agreed to a deal with [[Anadia F.C.|Anadia FC]] in the [[Liga 3 (Portugal)|Liga 3]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://afatv.pt/noticia/a-bitola-alta-do-anadia-fc-para-atacar-a-liga-3|title=A bitola alta do Anadia FC para atacar a Liga 3|trans-title=The high stakes of Anadia FC to attack Liga 3|publisher=AFA TV|language=pt|date=14 July 2021|accessdate=8 July 2024}}</ref> The following 26 January, he moved to Campeonato de Portugal side [[Länk FC Vilaverdense]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ojogo.pt/futebol/nao-profissional/noticias/brian-cipenga-e-reforco-do-lank-vilaverdense--14530382.html/|title=Brian Cipenga é reforço do Länk Vilaverdense|trans-title=Brian Cipenga is an addition of Länk Vilaverdense|publisher=[[O Jogo]]|language=pt|date=26 January 2022|accessdate=8 July 2024}}</ref> and helped in their promotion to Liga 3 at the end of [[2021–22 Campeonato de Portugal|the season]].

On 21 June 2023, Cipenga was announced at [[Liga Portugal 2]] side [[F.C. Paços de Ferreira|FC Paços de Ferreira]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.record.pt/futebol/futebol-nacional/2--liga/p--ferreira/detalhe/brian-cipenga-e-reforco-do-p-ferreira|title=Brian Cipenga é reforço do P. Ferreira|trans-title=Brian Cipenga is an addition of P. Ferreira|publisher=[[Record (Portuguese newspaper)|Record]]|language=pt|date=21 June 2023|accessdate=8 July 2024}}</ref> He made his professional debut on 12 August, starting in a 0–0 home draw against [[U.D. Leiria|União de Leiria]], and scored his first goal fourteen days later, in a 5–1 home routing of [[C.D. Tondela|CD Tondela]].

On 6 July 2024, Cipenga moved abroad and joined Spanish [[Segunda División]] side [[CD Castellón]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cdcastellon.com/brian-cipenga-nuevo-jugador-del-cd-castellon/|title=Brian Cipenga, nuevo jugador del CD Castellón|trans-title=Brian Cipenga, new player of CD Castellón|publisher=CD Castellón|language=es|date=6 July 2024|accessdate=8 July 2024}}</ref>

==International career==
Cipenga was called up to the [[DR Congo national football team|DR Congo national team]] for a set of [[2026 FIFA World Cup qualification]] matches in October 2025.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.congoquotidien.com/2025/10/07/brian-cipenga-selection-leopards-rdc-football/|title=Brian Cipenga, la surprise de Desabre pour les Léopards|date=7 October 2025}}</ref> He was part of the DR Congo national football team squad that secured qualification for the FIFA World Cup after a historic 1–0 victory over Jamaica national football team, sealed by a 100th-minute goal from Axel Tuanzebe, marking the nation’s first World Cup appearance in 52 years.

